(secondQuint)A Study Comparing Remimazolam Tosilate and Propofol for Intravenous General Anaesthesia in Operations.

 This is an multi-center,double-blinded,parallel and control study using Remimazolam or propofol for anesthesia in operations.

Subjects are randomized to different treatment groups (including 3 for Remimazolam Tosilate and 1 for propofol) and anaesthetics are pumped contimuously into bodies.

Analgesics and muscle relaxants are permitted during operations.

Efficacy,safety and pharmacokinetic/pharmacodynamic profiles of Remimazolam Tosilate are to be evaluated.

